Build instructions
1) ./configure --with-apache=/path/to/apache
2) make
3) su -c "make install"

*NOTE* If you are using Apache 2.0.47 or less you may get errors about
PACKAGE_NAME, PACKAGE_VERSION, etc... being redefined in config.h.. If you do, 
then you need to edit your ap_config_auto.h in your Apache include file and
un define or comment out the macros. ie.
Change
/* Define to the full name of this package. */
#define PACKAGE_NAME "httpd"
To
/* Define to the full name of this package. */
/* #define PACKAGE_NAME "httpd" */
Do that for all of the PACKAGE_* defines (BUGREPORT, NAME, STRING, TARNAME, 
VERSION).  Apache 2.0.48 does not have those lines so it is safe to remove 
them.

a sample config entry

Listen 21
<VirtualHost *:21>
	DocumentRoot /var/ftp
	FTPprotocol On
	FTPShowRealPermissions Off
	FTPAllowActive On
	FTPMinPort 1024
	FTPPaxPort 65535
	<Directory /var/ftp>
	   AuthDBMUserFile /usr/local/httpd/ftp
	   AuthName ftp
	   AuthType Basic
	   require valid-user
	</Directory>
</VirtualHost>
